        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Watch issued June 28 at 4:02PM EDT until June 28 at 8:00PM EDT by NWS Pittsburgh PA</headline>
        <description>THE NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE HAS EXTENDED SEVERE THUNDERSTORM
WATCH 471 TO INCLUDE THE FOLLOWING AREAS UNTIL 8 PM EDT THIS
EVENING

IN OHIO THIS WATCH INCLUDES 5 COUNTIES

IN EAST CENTRAL OHIO

BELMONT               GUERNSEY              MONROE
MUSKINGUM             NOBLE

IN PENNSYLVANIA THIS WATCH INCLUDES 4 COUNTIES

IN SOUTHWEST PENNSYLVANIA

ALLEGHENY             FAYETTE               GREENE
WASHINGTON

IN WEST VIRGINIA THIS WATCH INCLUDES 4 COUNTIES

IN NORTHERN WEST VIRGINIA

WETZEL

IN THE NORTHERN PANHANDLE OF WEST VIRGINIA

BROOKE                MARSHALL              OHIO

THIS INCLUDES THE CITIES OF CALDWELL, CAMBRIDGE, CANONSBURG,
CONNELLSVILLE, FOLLANSBEE, MARTINS FERRY, MASONTOWN, MOUNDSVILLE,
NEW MARTINSVILLE, PITTSBURGH METRO AREA, ST. CLAIRSVILLE,
UNIONTOWN, WASHINGTON, WAYNESBURG, WELLSBURG, WHEELING,
WOODSFIELD, AND ZANESVILLE.
</description>
